\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.1}{\ignorespaces Top-down view illustrating the difference between step-and-shoot and continuous scanning. In step-and-shoot mode the sample is stationary during each exposure (discrete coloured wedges). In continuous mode the sample rotates throughout, and each projection integrates over a swept angular interval (extended coloured arcs).\relax }}{51}{figure.caption.36}%
